entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: hi i am ellie thanks for coming in today i was created to talk to people in a safe and secure environment i am not a therapist but i am here to learn about people and would love to learn about you i will ask a few questions to get us started and please feel free to tell me anything your answers are totally confidential are you ok with this

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay so how are you doing today

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am okay i am feeling a little tired and worried

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i am looking for a place to live and i do not have a job right now so things are things are a little shaky for me

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i am sorry to hear that it can be tough to find a good job these days where do you live

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am staying with my son in venice

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i understand where are you from originally

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: originally from new york but i have been in california since the early seventies so

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is a long time

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why did you move to la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i moved to la because i had been living in portland oregon and i was getting tired of the weather up there and my son was down here so it seemed like a good place to be

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how easy was it for you to get used to living in la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it was not too hard i i met people right away and i just really like it here so it was it was easy to connect with people

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good what are some things you really like about la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the weather is nber one like for most people i love being near the ocean i like the energy i like the i like the artistic culture

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: wow

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah that was a fun trip

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how did you decide to do that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well we would been working together on the census and she had made that trip a few times and invited me to come along with her

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what is one of your most memorable experiences

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: from that trip i would say we were in oaxaca for day of the dead so it was celebrating day of the dead with the family in the little village that we were staying in and everybody in the village makes an altar in their house for their loved ones who have passed away and they also decorate clean and decorate the graves so there were lots of flowers and it was just it was neat to be there and be with that family celebrating that

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: awesome what did you study at school

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i studied i was in the liberal liberal arts program but i did not stay i stayed only stayed in school for in college for a couple of years but i was most interested in liberal arts and the hanities

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what is your dream job

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: h my dream job would be personal assisting somebody who was in a creative field and getting to travel and go to events with them

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good do you consider yourself more shy or outgoing

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am fairly i am kind of a friendly introvert so i i am you know i have no trouble meeting people i do not hold back and you know xxx just i am not shy like shy at parties i will go up and talk to people but i i am overall kind of introverted so i prefer one on one than big groups

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay sometimes when i am feeling tense i turn on the fish tank screensaver hey i know it is not hawaii but it is the best i have got what do you do to relax

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i like to watch well i i like to watch improvement shows like on hgtv i like to watch like remodel shows and and see transformations or or watch movies or read oh and and i play some solitaire on my my kindle fire

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i do not usually realize i am mad until later so it does not really come up and i i just tend not to have the kind of life where those situations arise sometimes you know sometimes on the road i get a little annoyed i do not get annoyed so much at like when people cut me off or anything like that but when people are deliberately rude and and you know honk for no reason or you know when they get angry because maybe i have done something inadvertent you know cut them off by mistake and they you know like they get really angry then that makes me angry in return

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: h yeah like i said i do not really get into argents i did have i was with a friend the other day and she got annoyed with me because she felt like i was correcting her so it was not really an argent but she you know i had said something that she heard as a correction well it was a correction and she got angry but

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how did you feel in that moment

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well then i felt criticized and i felt i felt vulnerable eh i was not it was it was pretty uncomfortable

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h tell me about a situation that you wish you had handled differently

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: h well i in that situation i did not i did not have to correct her so i think that is something i am starting to look at in myself is my need to be right so in general that is i am trying to to catch that and just let people make mistakes without without my telling them about it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see tell me about an event or something that you wish you could erase from your memory

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: h see gee that is tough if i do not really eh the the erasing from the memory part there is nothing i really wish i could erase from my memory trying to think of something that i have done that i wish i had not done oh okay i remember something there was there was a time when i was i was in a class at junior college it was a film class and i was i was the one who was after we we went out and did a little film project and we are supposed to bring it back into class the next week i was the one who had the film and through different just things that were happening in my life right now i never went back to the school but i never brought them the film back so all the work they had done they had to do over again and i still feel bad about that

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: oh no how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: eh it is pretty easy sometimes i wake up in the early morning hours and and have trouble going back to sleep but that is not very often

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i have been feeling kind of tired and low level depressed and like not feeling a lot of options

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes i have

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how long ago were you diagnosed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well there were two times there was once back in like nineteen seventy two nineteen yeah about nine nineteen seventy two or three and then another time oh so then when would that have been about sixteen years ago

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what got you to seek help

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: just feeling like there was not you know feeling that feeling that things were not gonna change if i did not get some help and that if i i did not have to you know that maybe if some i got some medication that would help me in the short term so
